playerpromo_verbal: With the varied, but limited tools available, I believe this paperclip should win due to the intricacy and detail presented, and how realistic it is. Thank you!
simple yet effective.   Spring has sprung!

This illustration encapsulates the word "show". But why? The dictionary definition of show gives several examples of the word... "allowing something to be visable, this could be a physical or an emotional entity", "a spectacle or display", "demonstration or proving", or in this percieved illustarted sense "a play or stage performance". But when you consider the word show within the performance show, the individual is physically and emotionally showing the audience something. They are demonstrating or proving their ability to show the audience what they mean or how they feel. What is more, through the spectacle they are performing, they are showing an outward appearance or display. This illustration isn't just the percieved show that you see, it is always much more.
I have very little artistic ability but this was all I could come up with. I was thinking about tea when participating in this study haha
Who doesn't love a snowman!? Instantly recognisable, cute and fun for all the family. Just looking at him makes me smile. Smile and enjoy my snowman.  :o)
I had Harry Potter in my head as soon as I seen the circles. its a pretty basic picture, I fully understand if not chosen.
This beautiful, strong piece of nature provides oxygen to our air, beauty to the earth and fun for children to climb or swing on.
I think this fish uses almost all of the given shapes creatively.
Its a make believe boy looking up at the sky for inspiration. He cannot decide where to go next
The word I illustrated represent all humans, we all have a face. My illustration is clear to see and read.

playerpromo_verbal: A colourful piece of artwork that includes several colours in order for the picture to stand out

I think that I have been creative in the way that I have used the shapes and colours at my disposal. I've gone the extra mile to create a tree to signify the importance of the way we look after our environment. We need to take care of our plants so that animals, i.e. my giraffe below will have food to eat.
I have illustrated an apple tree, creatively using the shapes given to me to represent the rounded bushy image of apple trees in their natural habitat
I illustrated a cupcake, because I believe everyone loves a small mini cake. It would look more pretty if i was able to color in the circle but I had to work with what I got.
I tried my best with my illustration and it looks as if it would be somewhat functional and hopefully recognizable!
